  "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "description": "<h3>In this role, you can expect to:</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work with a mix of cloud infrastructure and open-source technologies to build, scale, and maintain external and internal applications.</li>\n  <li>Design, build, and maintain APIs using either serverless or container technologies such as Kubernetes.</li>\n  <li>Architect, implement, and maintain front-end applications serving a mix of external and internal users, covering a variety of business use-cases.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with engineers in a project-oriented and agile-driven environment working across multiple product areas.</li>\n  <li>Work with the “you build it, you run it” mindset, enabled by a Platform Engineering team.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>You may be a good fit if:</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>You have spent around eight years working with JavaScript frameworks such as ReactJS or VueJS.</li>\n  <li>You have similar experience working with backend languages such as Python, Java, NodeJS, or Go.</li>\n  <li>You have built solutions on AWS using technologies such as Docker, Kubernetes, AWS Fargate, and AWS Lambda, and Terraform.</li>\n  <li>You have familiarity with database technologies such as MySQL, ElasticSearch (or OpenSearch), DynamoDB, MongoDB, or Cassandra.</li>\n  <li>You have worked with projects and teams which promote and use CI/CD pipelines.</li>\n</ul>",
